President Uhuru Kenyatta is this week expected to embark on a tour of the lower eastern counties of Machakos, Kitui, and Makueni. The tour scheduled to start on Tuesday coming at a time a section of leaders of the moribund NASA coalition had accused the head of state of taking goodies to his handshake partner Raila Odinga's region neglecting the other NASA strongholds. And as Geff Kirui reports the president is also expected this month to tour his deputy William Ruto's backyard of rift valley amidst serious fallout between the two.